## üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)

**1.** Encryption is the process of:
A. Copying data
B. Converting plaintext into ciphertext
C. Compressing data
D. Deleting data

**2.** Plaintext refers to:
A. Encrypted data
B. Original readable data
C. Compressed data
D. Backup data

**3.** Ciphertext is:
A. Readable message
B. Encrypted message
C. Decrypted data
D. Key

**4.** Which element is REQUIRED for encryption?
A. Algorithm
B. Key
C. Plaintext
D. All of the above

**5.** Encryption mainly ensures:
A. Availability
B. Integrity
C. Confidentiality
D. Authentication

**6.** File encryption protects:
A. Network traffic
B. Stored files
C. User passwords only
D. Hardware

**7.** Which OS provides built-in file encryption?
A. DOS
B. Windows
C. All modern OS
D. None

**8.** Encrypted folder means:
A. Folder hidden
B. Folder compressed
C. Folder contents encrypted
D. Folder deleted

**9.** `cipher` command in Windows is used to:
A. Compress files
B. Encrypt/decrypt files and folders
C. Delete files
D. Backup files

**10.** Which is a graphical way to encrypt a folder in Windows?
A. Command Prompt
B. Properties ‚Üí Advanced ‚Üí Encrypt
C. Registry Editor
D. Task Manager

---

## üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)

**11.** Encryption without key is:
A. Strong
B. Weak
C. Impossible
D. Optional

**12.** Which encryption protects data at rest?
A. Network encryption
B. File encryption
C. SSL
D. TLS

**13.** Which Windows feature uses EFS?
A. NTFS
B. FAT32
C. exFAT
D. ReFS only

**14.** `cipher /e` command does what?
A. Decrypts files
B. Encrypts files
C. Deletes files
D. Compresses files

**15.** Which command decrypts encrypted files?
A. `cipher /d`
B. `cipher /e`
C. `cipher /c`
D. `cipher /x`

**16.** Which key is used in file encryption by default in Windows EFS?
A. Public key only
B. Private key only
C. Symmetric key protected by user certificate
D. No key

**17.** What happens if encryption certificate is lost?
A. File remains accessible
B. File becomes unreadable
C. File auto-decrypts
D. File is deleted

**18.** Which folder encryption applies encryption to sub-files?
A. No folder supports this
B. Only file-level
C. Folder-level encryption
D. Compression

**19.** Which is TRUE about EFS?
A. Works on FAT32
B. Works only on NTFS
C. Encrypts entire disk
D. Requires internet

**20.** Which encryption scope protects entire drive?
A. File encryption
B. Folder encryption
C. Disk encryption (BitLocker)
D. Compression

---

## üî∫ ADVANCED LEVEL MCQs (10)

**21.** File encryption mainly protects against:
A. Network sniffing
B. Unauthorized file access
C. DoS attack
D. Spoofing

**22.** Encryption folders are BEST used when:
A. Files change frequently
B. Files are temporary
C. Multiple sensitive files exist
D. No security needed

**23.** `cipher /w` command is used to:
A. Encrypt files
B. Decrypt files
C. Overwrite deleted data
D. Backup encryption key

**24.** Which is NOT true about file encryption?
A. Protects data at rest
B. Needs key management
C. Protects during transmission
D. Depends on OS support

**25.** Which attack is mitigated by file encryption?
A. Insider theft
B. Data theft from stolen disk
C. DoS
D. Replay attack

**26.** Which encryption approach allows transparency to user?
A. Manual file encryption
B. Folder-based encryption
C. Application-level encryption
D. Network encryption

**27.** Loss of private key affects:
A. Encryption only
B. Decryption only
C. Both
D. None

**28.** Which command displays encryption status?
A. `cipher /e`
B. `cipher /d`
C. `cipher /c`
D. `cipher /s`

**29.** Which is a limitation of file-level encryption?
A. Complex setup
B. No protection for backups
C. High bandwidth usage
D. Requires internet

**30.** CCEE MOST COMMON TRAP in encryption is:
A. Plaintext vs Ciphertext
B. File vs Disk encryption
C. `cipher /e` vs `cipher /d`
D. All of the above

